WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.088 --> 00:00:09.091
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:09.175 --> 00:00:11.970
♪ ♪

3
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:54.803
♪ ♪

5
00:01:47.565 --> 00:01:49.526
(light music playing)

6
00:01:49.608 --> 00:01:52.444
(wind blowing)

7
00:02:15.717 --> 00:02:18.763
♪ ♪

8
00:02:28.815 --> 00:02:30.567
Princess Rhaenyra:
There you are.

9
00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:43.121
The Sea Snake is
going to die. isn't he?

10
00:02:45.163 --> 00:02:48.251
- Luke...
- I can't be Lord of the Tides.

11
00:02:48.334 --> 00:02:50.919
Grand sire was the greatest
sailor who ever lived.

12
00:02:51.003 --> 00:02:53.548
I get green sick before the ship

13
00:02:53.631 --> 00:02:55.424
even leaves the harbor.

14
00:02:55.508 --> 00:02:57.384
I'll just ruin everything.

15
00:02:58.511 --> 00:03:00.888
I don't want Driftmark.

16
00:03:00.972 --> 00:03:02.452
It should've passed on
to Ser Vaemond.

17
00:03:02.514 --> 00:03:05.727
We don't choose our
destiny. Luke. It chooses us.

18
00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:08.770
Grand sire let you choose
whether you'd be his heir.

19
00:03:09.688 --> 00:03:10.982
You told us so.

20
00:03:15.485 --> 00:03:18.197
And do you want
to know the truth of it?

21
00:03:21.158 --> 00:03:22.785
I was frightened.

22
00:03:24.245 --> 00:03:26.705
I was... four-and-ten.

23
00:03:26.788 --> 00:03:29.167
Same as you are now.

24
00:03:29.918 --> 00:03:31.169
I wasn't ready

25
00:03:31.251 --> 00:03:34.422
to be Queen
of the Seven Kingdoms.

26
00:03:34.505 --> 00:03:37.717
But... it was my duty.

27
00:03:37.799 --> 00:03:40.261
And. in time.
I came to understand

28
00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:42.597
I had to earn my inheritance.

29
00:03:44.389 --> 00:03:45.934
I'm not like you.

30
00:03:46.017 --> 00:03:48.186
- In what way. sweet boy?
- I'm not so...

31
00:03:51.229 --> 00:03:54.275
perfect.

32
00:03:58.947 --> 00:04:00.239
(kisses)

33
00:04:01.323 --> 00:04:05.495
- I am anything but.
- (footsteps approach)

34
00:04:05.578 --> 00:04:06.329
My father looked after me

35
00:04:06.412 --> 00:04:09.414
and helped to prepare me
for my duties.

36
00:04:09.499 --> 00:04:13.335
Your mother will do
the same for you.

37
00:04:13.418 --> 00:04:15.003
Lorent Marbrand:
Good morrow. Princess.

38
00:04:15.087 --> 00:04:17.924
Good morrow. Ser Lorent.

39
00:04:18.006 --> 00:04:19.734
Princess Rhaenys has
just arrived on dragon back.

40
00:04:19.758 --> 00:04:23.304
She urgently requests an audience
with you and Prince Daemon.

41
00:04:30.061 --> 00:04:31.645
(door opens)

42
00:04:41.780 --> 00:04:43.907
The Princess Rhaenys Targaryen.

43
00:04:43.991 --> 00:04:45.575
Thank you. Ser Lorent.

44
00:04:49.580 --> 00:04:51.206
Princess Rhaenys...

45
00:04:51.289 --> 00:04:54.085
might we hope for news
of Lord Corlys's recovery?

46
00:04:54.167 --> 00:04:55.210
Viserys is dead.

47
00:04:57.839 --> 00:05:00.633
♪ ♪

48
00:05:01.967 --> 00:05:04.679
I grieve this loss with you.
Rhaenyra.

49
00:05:04.761 --> 00:05:07.849
My cousin. your father...

50
00:05:09.224 --> 00:05:10.309
possessed a kind heart.

51
00:05:21.987 --> 00:05:24.239
There is more.

52
00:05:24.323 --> 00:05:27.243
Aegon has been crowned
as his successor.

53
00:05:28.828 --> 00:05:31.121
(whimpers)

54
00:05:34.708 --> 00:05:36.544
They crowned him?

55
00:05:38.046 --> 00:05:40.590
How did Viserys die?

56
00:05:40.672 --> 00:05:42.883
I could not say.

57
00:05:42.967 --> 00:05:45.052
- How long ago?
- A day past. perhaps two.

58
00:05:45.136 --> 00:05:46.155
I was made a prisoner
in my quarters

59
00:05:46.179 --> 00:05:47.013
while the Queen
made her preparations.

60
00:05:47.095 --> 00:05:48.263
Viserys has been slain.

61
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:55.645
Alicent demanded
you declare for Aegon.

62
00:05:56.938 --> 00:05:59.984
She did.

63
00:06:00.859 --> 00:06:03.780
- I refused her.
- And yet you are alive.

64
00:06:06.532 --> 00:06:10.285
The High Septon crowned Aegon
in the Dragon pit.

65
00:06:10.369 --> 00:06:13.289
I witnessed it myself
just before I fled on Meleys.

66
00:06:13.371 --> 00:06:15.874
They crowned him
before the masses.

67
00:06:15.958 --> 00:06:19.087
Princess Rhaenys: So that the masses
would see him as their rightful king.

68
00:06:19.169 --> 00:06:22.381
That whore of a Queen murdered
my brother and stole his throne.

69
00:06:22.465 --> 00:06:25.051
And you could have
burned them all for it.

70
00:06:25.133 --> 00:06:27.453
A war is like to be fought
over this treachery. to be sure.

71
00:06:28.845 --> 00:06:30.597
Mm.

72
00:06:32.182 --> 00:06:35.143
But that war is
not mine to begin.

73
00:06:35.227 --> 00:06:37.188
I only rushed
this warning to you

74
00:06:37.270 --> 00:06:39.773
out of loyalty to my
husband and to my house.

75
00:06:42.068 --> 00:06:44.027
The Greens are coming
for you. Rhaenyra.

76
00:06:45.237 --> 00:06:46.321
And for your children.

77
00:06:48.407 --> 00:06:50.450
You should leave
Dragons tone at once.

78
00:06:50.535 --> 00:06:52.619
(tense music playing)

79
00:06:53.453 --> 00:06:56.039
(whimpers. gasps)

80
00:07:10.138 --> 00:07:12.640
The babe is coming.

81
00:07:12.722 --> 00:07:15.059
(breathing heavily)

82
00:07:15.684 --> 00:07:17.352
(Rhaenyra groaning)

83
00:07:20.105 --> 00:07:21.165
Her term is far from complete.

84
00:07:21.189 --> 00:07:23.818
This should not be happening.

85
00:07:23.900 --> 00:07:26.736
It is fucking happening.

86
00:07:26.821 --> 00:07:30.448
Older Midwife: Keep your
head about you. Princess. Come.

87
00:07:30.532 --> 00:07:33.994
Elinda: We've done
this five times before.

88
00:07:34.078 --> 00:07:36.455
Keep your spirit. and the
sixth will be no different.

89
00:07:36.539 --> 00:07:38.916
Get off. get off.
get off. get off!

90
00:07:38.999 --> 00:07:41.835
Ow. ow. ow. (Gasps)

91
00:07:45.297 --> 00:07:47.049
I want patrols along
the island's perimeter.

92
00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:50.511
looking for any small ships
that might set ashore.

93
00:07:50.595 --> 00:07:52.847
If the Greens attack now.
it will be by stealth...

94
00:07:52.929 --> 00:07:54.931
- (Rhaenyra groaning)
- ...not directly.

95
00:07:55.015 --> 00:07:56.826
We don't have enough men
to surround the island.

96
00:07:56.850 --> 00:07:59.520
but we can make ourselves
appear stronger than they are.

97
00:07:59.604 --> 00:08:02.982
(Rhaenyra screaming)

98
00:08:03.064 --> 00:08:04.542
Conscript the Dragon keepers.
They're capable fighters.

99
00:08:04.566 --> 00:08:06.986
- Waste no time.
- It will be done. my Prince.

100
00:08:07.068 --> 00:08:11.032
(Rhaenyra screaming)

101
00:08:11.114 --> 00:08:13.575
- (grunting)
- (swords clanging)

102
00:08:19.999 --> 00:08:23.919
- What was that?
- (grunts) I'm sorry.

103
00:08:24.003 --> 00:08:25.962
You might go easier

104
00:08:26.047 --> 00:08:27.797
on him. my Prince.

105
00:08:27.881 --> 00:08:29.359
so he can learn what
you're trying to teach.

106
00:08:29.383 --> 00:08:32.845
Rhaenys: Your lady
mother needs to see you!

107
00:08:34.846 --> 00:08:36.514
Both of you.

108
00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:39.268
- (gasps)
- Prince Jacaerys: Mother?

109
00:08:39.351 --> 00:08:42.229
(Rhaenyra groaning)

110
00:08:42.312 --> 00:08:43.898
Rhaenyra: Fuck.

111
00:08:45.358 --> 00:08:47.734
Maester Gerardys: Princess.

112
00:08:51.196 --> 00:08:54.282
♪ ♪

113
00:08:58.745 --> 00:09:01.040
Your grand sire.
King Viserys. has passed.

114
00:09:01.123 --> 00:09:02.457
V-Viserys?

115
00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:05.503
The Greens have
repudiated the succession

116
00:09:05.585 --> 00:09:07.338
and claimed the Iron Throne.

117
00:09:11.383 --> 00:09:13.176
Aegon has been crowned king.

118
00:09:14.552 --> 00:09:16.471
- What is to be done about it?
- Nothing yet.

119
00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:20.017
- And where is Daemon?
- Rhaenyra: I don't know.

120
00:09:20.100 --> 00:09:21.686
Gone to madness.

121
00:09:23.896 --> 00:09:25.189
Gone to plot his war.

122
00:09:26.398 --> 00:09:29.277
- Jacaerys: Leave Daemon with me.
- Rhaenyra: Jace.

123
00:09:30.069 --> 00:09:31.195
Jacaerys.

124
00:09:36.783 --> 00:09:40.454
Whatever claim remains to me.
you are now its heir.

125
00:09:40.537 --> 00:09:43.541
Naught is to be done
but by my command.

126
00:09:51.882 --> 00:09:53.426
(groaning)

127
00:09:57.763 --> 00:10:00.016
Bartimos Celtigar:
A raven flew in this morning.

128
00:10:00.099 --> 00:10:01.599
The Sea Snake's
fever has broken.

129
00:10:01.683 --> 00:10:03.476
and he has left Even fall.

130
00:10:03.561 --> 00:10:06.980
- Where is he sailing?
- That much is unclear. my Prince.

131
00:10:07.064 --> 00:10:08.858
We'll send ravens
to our nearest allies:

132
00:10:08.941 --> 00:10:12.152
Lords Darklyn. Massey...

133
00:10:12.235 --> 00:10:15.364
- and Bar Emmon.
- Rhaenyra: (shouts) Daemon!

134
00:10:15.447 --> 00:10:17.700
Do you want to speak
to the maester. my Prince?

135
00:10:25.499 --> 00:10:27.752
I'll fly to
the River lands myself

136
00:10:27.835 --> 00:10:29.170
and affirm Lord Tully's support.

137
00:10:29.253 --> 00:10:30.837
You will do no such thing.

138
00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:36.551
My mother has decreed no
action be taken while she's abed.

139
00:10:43.058 --> 00:10:45.561
It's good you're here.
young Prince.

140
00:10:45.643 --> 00:10:48.564
You're needed to patrol
the skies on Vermax.

141
00:10:48.648 --> 00:10:49.230
Did you hear what I said?

142
00:10:49.315 --> 00:10:52.651
(Rhaenyra screaming)

143
00:10:53.360 --> 00:10:54.778
The ravens. Lord Bartimos.

144
00:10:58.114 --> 00:10:59.114
I shall see it done.

145
00:10:59.157 --> 00:11:00.743
Summon Ser Steffon.

146
00:11:00.825 --> 00:11:03.912
Our Kings guard are needed
on the Dragonmont.

147
00:11:03.995 --> 00:11:07.041
Come with me. I'll show you
the true meaning of loyalty.

148
00:11:13.839 --> 00:11:17.426
You swore an oath
as knights of the Kings guard.

149
00:11:17.509 --> 00:11:19.970
As do all who wear
the white cloak. my Prince.

150
00:11:21.430 --> 00:11:23.724
To whom?

151
00:11:23.807 --> 00:11:27.728
I swore first to King
Jaehaerys. my Prince.

152
00:11:27.811 --> 00:11:29.021
And then to His Grace.

153
00:11:29.104 --> 00:11:31.356
King Viserys.
when he succeeded him.

154
00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:33.280
Do you acknowledge
the true line of succession?

155
00:11:34.234 --> 00:11:36.070
- Yes.
- Yes. my Prince.

156
00:11:36.152 --> 00:11:37.654
♪ ♪

157
00:11:42.826 --> 00:11:44.702
Do you recall...

158
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:48.499
who King Viserys named
as his heir before his death?

159
00:11:51.042 --> 00:11:53.962
Princess Rhaenyra.

160
00:11:54.046 --> 00:11:55.880
Hm.

161
00:11:55.965 --> 00:11:59.676
I'm grateful for your long
service to the crown.

162
00:12:00.635 --> 00:12:03.388
So I'm presenting you
with a choice.

163
00:12:03.471 --> 00:12:05.557
(Caraxes screeches)

164
00:12:14.483 --> 00:12:16.067
(roars)

165
00:12:20.864 --> 00:12:23.658
♪ ♪

166
00:12:25.952 --> 00:12:30.832
Swear anew your oath
to Rhaenyra as your queen...

167
00:12:30.916 --> 00:12:33.335
to Prince Jacaerys as
the heir to the Iron Throne.

168
00:12:33.418 --> 00:12:36.839
(groaning. breathing heavily)

169
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:40.216
- (roars)
- Prince Daemon: Or...

170
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:41.981
if you support the usurper.
speak it now...

171
00:12:44.345 --> 00:12:46.146
and you will have a clean
and honorable death.

172
00:12:47.849 --> 00:12:50.186
But if you choose treachery.

173
00:12:50.268 --> 00:12:53.730
if you swear fealty now only
to later turn your cloaks...

174
00:12:56.441 --> 00:12:59.402
know that you will die...

175
00:12:59.487 --> 00:13:00.487
screaming.

176
00:13:00.528 --> 00:13:01.864
(screams)

177
00:13:01.946 --> 00:13:03.072
(roars)

178
00:13:03.532 --> 00:13:04.908
(grunting)

179
00:13:06.619 --> 00:13:07.744
Princess. let us help you.

180
00:13:11.123 --> 00:13:12.999
- (groans) No.
- (growls)

181
00:13:15.418 --> 00:13:18.087
- (screams) Get out!
- Elinda: Princess. please.

182
00:13:18.172 --> 00:13:20.108
- Get out.
- You should not do this alone. Princess.

183
00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:21.132
Let us help you.

184
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:22.759
(cries)

185
00:13:24.010 --> 00:13:25.345
(gasps)

186
00:13:28.224 --> 00:13:29.807
(screams)

187
00:13:38.816 --> 00:13:40.402
(screaming)

188
00:13:42.904 --> 00:13:44.739
(breathing heavily)

189
00:13:48.952 --> 00:13:50.204
(gasps)

190
00:14:00.380 --> 00:14:01.965
(cries)

191
00:14:04.093 --> 00:14:05.927
(breathing heavily)

192
00:14:25.739 --> 00:14:27.825
(somber music playing)

193
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:43.090
♪ ♪

194
00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:21.503
(waves crashing)

195
00:15:21.586 --> 00:15:25.048
♪ ♪

196
00:15:58.289 --> 00:16:01.335
♪ ♪

197
00:16:20.812 --> 00:16:23.190
(flames crackling)

198
00:16:46.337 --> 00:16:48.047
Erryk Cargyll:
I mean no harm. brothers.

199
00:17:05.524 --> 00:17:09.402
(light strings playing)

200
00:17:11.529 --> 00:17:13.198
I swear to ward the Queen...

201
00:17:16.034 --> 00:17:17.661
with all my strength...

202
00:17:18.953 --> 00:17:21.789
and give my blood for hers.

203
00:17:26.711 --> 00:17:28.797
I shall take no wife...

204
00:17:29.547 --> 00:17:31.883
hold no lands...

205
00:17:33.301 --> 00:17:34.635
father no children.

206
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:37.890
I shall guard her secrets...

207
00:17:38.556 --> 00:17:41.434
obey her commands...

208
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:45.021
ride at her side. and
defend her name and honor.

209
00:17:52.946 --> 00:17:55.490
♪ ♪

210
00:17:57.950 --> 00:17:59.995
♪ ♪

211
00:18:10.631 --> 00:18:12.048
My Queen.

212
00:18:26.395 --> 00:18:30.400
(regal music playing)

213
00:18:50.546 --> 00:18:54.341
♪ ♪

214
00:19:18.114 --> 00:19:20.158
♪ ♪

215
00:19:55.192 --> 00:19:59.072
Daemon: Queen Rhaenyra
Targaryen. First of Her Name.

216
00:19:59.155 --> 00:20:03.160
Queen of the Andals and
the Rhoynar and the First Men.

217
00:20:03.242 --> 00:20:06.787
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms
and Protector of the Realm.

218
00:20:10.499 --> 00:20:12.001
Your Grace.

219
00:20:20.552 --> 00:20:22.386
Wine. my Queen.

220
00:20:25.265 --> 00:20:26.600
Thank you. Rhaena.

221
00:20:27.558 --> 00:20:28.768
Come.

222
00:20:53.250 --> 00:20:54.270
- What is our standing?
- Daemon: We have 30 knights.

223
00:20:54.294 --> 00:20:57.838
a hundred crossbowmen.
and 300 men-at-arms.

224
00:20:57.922 --> 00:20:59.674
Dragons tone is
relatively easy to defend.

225
00:20:59.758 --> 00:21:01.038
but as an instrument
of conquest.

226
00:21:01.093 --> 00:21:03.345
our army leaves
a lot to be desired.

227
00:21:03.428 --> 00:21:05.806
We have sent word to my
loyal men in the City Watch.

228
00:21:05.889 --> 00:21:06.806
I'll have some support there.

229
00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:08.076
but I cannot speak
to the numbers.

230
00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:11.018
We already have declarations
from Celtigar and St aunt on.

231
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:14.480
Massey. Darklyn. Bar Emmon.

232
00:21:17.108 --> 00:21:18.360
My lady mother was an Arryn.

233
00:21:18.442 --> 00:21:21.654
The Vale will not turn
cloak against their own kin.

234
00:21:21.738 --> 00:21:23.239
River run was
always a close friend

235
00:21:23.323 --> 00:21:25.158
to your father. Your Grace.

236
00:21:25.241 --> 00:21:26.910
With Prince Daemon's
acquiescence.

237
00:21:26.993 --> 00:21:29.287
I've already sent ravens
to Lord Grover.

238
00:21:32.415 --> 00:21:35.419
Lord Grover is fickle
and easily swayed.

239
00:21:35.501 --> 00:21:38.046
He will need to be convinced
of the strength of our position

240
00:21:38.130 --> 00:21:40.923
and that we will support him
should it come to war.

241
00:21:41.008 --> 00:21:43.009
I'm going to treat
with him myself.

242
00:21:43.093 --> 00:21:44.779
Steffon Darklyn: What of
Storm's End and Winter fell?

243
00:21:44.803 --> 00:21:47.389
Bartimos: There has never
lived a Stark who forgot an oath.

244
00:21:47.471 --> 00:21:50.307
And with House Stark.
the North will follow.

245
00:21:50.392 --> 00:21:54.062
Lord Borros Baratheon will need to
be reminded of his father's promises.

246
00:22:06.991 --> 00:22:09.118
What news from Driftmark?

247
00:22:11.829 --> 00:22:12.974
Lord Corlys sails
for Dragons tone.

248
00:22:12.998 --> 00:22:15.291
To declare for his Queen.

249
00:22:17.376 --> 00:22:20.463
The Velaryon fleet is
in my husband's yoke.

250
00:22:20.547 --> 00:22:22.423
He decides where they sail.

251
00:22:22.507 --> 00:22:25.677
Rhaenyra: We shall pray for both
you and your husband's support.

252
00:22:25.760 --> 00:22:28.930
Just as we prayed nightly for the
Sea Snake's return to good health.

253
00:22:30.181 --> 00:22:32.201
There's no port on the
Narrow Sea would dare to make

254
00:22:32.225 --> 00:22:33.465
an enemy of the Velaryon fleet.

255
00:22:36.438 --> 00:22:39.607
- And our enemies?
- We have no friends among the Lannisters.

256
00:22:39.691 --> 00:22:42.777
Tyland has served the Hand
too long to turn against him.

257
00:22:42.861 --> 00:22:45.113
And Otto High tower
needs the Lannister fleet.

258
00:22:45.197 --> 00:22:46.549
Without the Lannisters.
we are not like to find

259
00:22:46.573 --> 00:22:48.991
- any allies west of the Golden Tooth.
- Daemon: No.

260
00:22:52.245 --> 00:22:53.885
The River lands are
essential. Your Grace.

261
00:22:55.457 --> 00:22:57.209
Pray forgive my bluntness.
Your Grace.

262
00:22:57.291 --> 00:22:58.794
but talk of men is moot.

263
00:22:58.876 --> 00:23:01.587
Your cause owns a power

264
00:23:01.671 --> 00:23:03.422
that has not been
seen in this world

265
00:23:03.507 --> 00:23:06.008
since the days of Old Valyria.

266
00:23:06.093 --> 00:23:07.384
Dragons.

267
00:23:10.471 --> 00:23:11.972
The Greens have dragons as well.

268
00:23:12.056 --> 00:23:13.201
Daemon: They have
three adults. by my count.

269
00:23:13.225 --> 00:23:16.978
We have Syrax.
Caraxes. and Meleys.

270
00:23:17.062 --> 00:23:19.064
Your sons have Vermax.
Arrax. and Tyraxes.

271
00:23:19.146 --> 00:23:21.732
Baela has Moondancer.

272
00:23:21.816 --> 00:23:23.735
Daemon. none of our dragons
have been to war.

273
00:23:23.818 --> 00:23:25.778
There are also
unclaimed dragons.

274
00:23:25.862 --> 00:23:27.905
Sea smoke still
resides on Driftmark.

275
00:23:27.989 --> 00:23:30.866
Vermithor and Silver wing
dwell on the Dragonmont.

276
00:23:30.950 --> 00:23:33.161
still riderless.

277
00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:35.555
Then there are the three wild
dragons. all of whom nest here.

278
00:23:35.579 --> 00:23:36.998
Rhaenyra:
And who is to ride them?

279
00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:40.460
Daemon:
Dragons tone has 13 to their 4.

280
00:23:40.544 --> 00:23:43.587
I also have a score of eggs
incubating in the Dragonmont.

281
00:23:43.672 --> 00:23:47.217
Now... we need
a place to gather.

282
00:23:47.299 --> 00:23:50.845
a toehold large enough
to house a sizable host.

283
00:23:50.929 --> 00:23:52.721
Here. at Harrenhal.
We cut off the west.

284
00:23:52.806 --> 00:23:53.991
surround King's Landing
with the dragons.

285
00:23:54.015 --> 00:23:56.351
And we could have every
Green head mounted on spikes

286
00:23:56.433 --> 00:23:58.435
before the fucking moon turns.

287
00:23:58.519 --> 00:23:59.187
Your Grace...

288
00:23:59.270 --> 00:24:02.022
a ship has been
sighted offshore:

289
00:24:02.106 --> 00:24:03.126
A lone galleon. flying a banner

290
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:04.526
of a three-headed green dragon.

291
00:24:04.608 --> 00:24:06.736
Alert the watchtowers.
Sight the skies.

292
00:24:07.403 --> 00:24:10.824
(tense music playing)

293
00:24:32.929 --> 00:24:34.972
♪ ♪

294
00:24:43.647 --> 00:24:47.402
I come at the behest
of the Dowager Queen Alicent.

295
00:24:47.485 --> 00:24:49.696
mother of King Aegon.
Second of His Name.

296
00:24:49.778 --> 00:24:52.449
Lord and Protector
of the Seven Kingdoms.

297
00:24:52.531 --> 00:24:55.117
I've been directed
to deliver her message

298
00:24:55.201 --> 00:24:57.996
only to Princess Rhaenyra.

299
00:24:58.829 --> 00:25:01.082
Where is the Princess?

300
00:25:01.165 --> 00:25:03.210
(Syrax screeches)

301
00:25:05.879 --> 00:25:08.923
(roars)

302
00:25:12.844 --> 00:25:14.136
(screeches)

303
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:26.732
(roaring)

304
00:25:29.318 --> 00:25:32.029
(bellows)

305
00:25:39.246 --> 00:25:40.537
(roars)

306
00:25:55.010 --> 00:25:57.180
Princess Rhaenyra.

307
00:25:57.846 --> 00:26:00.933
I'm Queen Rhaenyra now.

308
00:26:01.017 --> 00:26:03.603
And you all are
traitors to the realm.

309
00:26:03.687 --> 00:26:07.649
King Aegon Targaryen.
Second of His Name...

310
00:26:09.358 --> 00:26:12.778
in his wisdom
and desire for peace.

311
00:26:12.862 --> 00:26:14.322
is offering terms.

312
00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:17.534
Acknowledge Aegon as king

313
00:26:17.616 --> 00:26:20.412
and swear obeisance
before the Iron Throne.

314
00:26:20.495 --> 00:26:22.329
In exchange.
His Grace will confirm

315
00:26:22.413 --> 00:26:25.874
your possession of Dragons tone.

316
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:27.585
It will pass
to your true born son.

317
00:26:27.669 --> 00:26:29.546
Jacaerys. upon your death.

318
00:26:29.629 --> 00:26:30.922
Lucerys will be confirmed

319
00:26:31.006 --> 00:26:32.923
as the legitimate
heir to Driftmark

320
00:26:33.008 --> 00:26:35.844
and all the lands and
holdings of House Velaryon.

321
00:26:35.926 --> 00:26:37.720
Your sons by Prince Daemon

322
00:26:37.804 --> 00:26:40.806
will also be given places
of high honor at court:

323
00:26:40.890 --> 00:26:43.351
Aegon the Younger
as the King's squire.

324
00:26:43.434 --> 00:26:44.518
Viserys as his cupbearer.

325
00:26:44.602 --> 00:26:47.521
Finally. the King.
in his good grace.

326
00:26:47.604 --> 00:26:49.941
will pardon any knight or lord

327
00:26:50.025 --> 00:26:52.693
who conspired
against his ascent.

328
00:26:52.777 --> 00:26:55.363
I would rather feed
my sons to the dragons

329
00:26:55.447 --> 00:26:58.533
than have them
carry shields and cups

330
00:26:58.615 --> 00:27:02.912
for your drunken.
usurper cunt of a king.

331
00:27:02.996 --> 00:27:06.415
Aegon Targaryen
sits the Iron Throne.

332
00:27:07.291 --> 00:27:08.436
He wears the Conqueror's crown.

333
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:10.210
wields the Conqueror's sword.

334
00:27:10.295 --> 00:27:12.505
has the Conqueror's name.

335
00:27:12.588 --> 00:27:15.383
He was anointed
by a septon of the Faith

336
00:27:15.467 --> 00:27:16.609
before the eyes of thousands.

337
00:27:16.633 --> 00:27:21.806
Every symbol of legitimacy
belongs to him.

338
00:27:23.932 --> 00:27:26.393
And then there is Stark.
Tully. Baratheon.

339
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:29.229
Houses that have also received.

340
00:27:29.314 --> 00:27:31.441
and are at present.

341
00:27:31.524 --> 00:27:34.568
considering generous terms
from their king.

342
00:27:36.321 --> 00:27:40.408
Stark. Tully. and Baratheon
all swore to me

343
00:27:40.491 --> 00:27:43.620
when King Viserys
named me his heir.

344
00:27:43.702 --> 00:27:48.415
Stale oaths will not put you
on the Iron Throne. Princess.

345
00:27:48.499 --> 00:27:52.002
The succession changed the day
your father sired a son.

346
00:27:52.086 --> 00:27:57.758
I only regret that you and he
were the last to see the truth of it.

347
00:27:57.842 --> 00:28:00.095
You are no more Hand
than Aegon is king.

348
00:28:00.178 --> 00:28:01.845
Fucking traitor.

349
00:28:13.691 --> 00:28:15.317
Grand Maester.

350
00:28:20.573 --> 00:28:21.658
What the fuck is this?

351
00:28:27.372 --> 00:28:28.706
(solemn music playing)

352
00:28:37.257 --> 00:28:39.497
Otto High tower: Queen
Alicent has not forgotten the love

353
00:28:39.550 --> 00:28:42.303
you once had for each other.

354
00:28:42.386 --> 00:28:44.346
No blood need be spilled.

355
00:28:44.431 --> 00:28:47.892
so the realm can
carry on in peace.

356
00:28:51.563 --> 00:28:52.915
Queen Alicent
eagerly awaits your answer.

357
00:28:52.939 --> 00:28:56.151
She can have her answer now.
stuffed in her father's mouth

358
00:28:56.233 --> 00:28:56.817
along with his withered cock.

359
00:28:56.901 --> 00:28:59.445
Let's end this mummer's farce.

360
00:29:00.904 --> 00:29:01.655
Ser Erryk.
bring me Lord High tower

361
00:29:01.739 --> 00:29:04.159
so I may take
the pleasure myself.

362
00:29:04.241 --> 00:29:06.243
(Syrax roars)

363
00:29:09.122 --> 00:29:10.248
No.

364
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:16.504
♪ ♪

365
00:29:21.968 --> 00:29:23.888
King's Landing will have
my answer on the morrow.

366
00:29:39.110 --> 00:29:40.612
(roars)

367
00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:49.746
Daemon: It's no easy thing
for a man to be a dragons layer.

368
00:29:49.828 --> 00:29:54.666
But dragons can kill dragons.
And have.

369
00:29:54.750 --> 00:29:57.961
The simple truth is this:
We have more dragons than Aegon.

370
00:29:58.046 --> 00:30:00.381
Viserys spoke often
of the Valyrian histories.

371
00:30:00.464 --> 00:30:02.758
I know them well.

372
00:30:02.842 --> 00:30:04.969
When dragons flew to war...

373
00:30:05.929 --> 00:30:07.346
everything burned.

374
00:30:09.473 --> 00:30:12.643
I do not wish to rule over
a kingdom of ash and bone.

375
00:30:12.727 --> 00:30:15.896
Are you considering the
High towers' terms. Your Grace?

376
00:30:15.979 --> 00:30:17.524
As Queen. what is my true duty

377
00:30:17.606 --> 00:30:20.235
to the realm. Lord Bartimos?

378
00:30:20.317 --> 00:30:21.736
Ensuring peace and unity?

379
00:30:21.818 --> 00:30:23.820
Or that I sit the Iron Throne.
no matter the cost?

380
00:30:23.904 --> 00:30:27.408
- That's your father talking.
- My father's dead.

381
00:30:29.201 --> 00:30:31.371
And he chose me
as his successor...

382
00:30:33.831 --> 00:30:36.375
to defend the realm.
not cast it headlong into war.

383
00:30:36.459 --> 00:30:37.770
Well. the enemy
have declared war.

384
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:40.255
What are you gonna do about it?

385
00:30:43.799 --> 00:30:44.842
Clear the room.

386
00:31:15.539 --> 00:31:17.040
Does the promise
of war excite you?

387
00:31:17.124 --> 00:31:18.918
You cannot bend the knee
to the High towers.

388
00:31:19.001 --> 00:31:19.751
They stole your birthright.

389
00:31:19.835 --> 00:31:22.255
If you could take
the Iron Throne

390
00:31:22.337 --> 00:31:24.507
without putting Otto
Hightower's head on a spike.

391
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:25.924
- would you?
- Are you not angry?

392
00:31:26.008 --> 00:31:28.428
- I should declare war because I'm angry?
- No.

393
00:31:28.510 --> 00:31:30.510
Because it's your duty
as Queen to crush rebellion.

394
00:31:30.555 --> 00:31:31.889
You know my oath

395
00:31:31.972 --> 00:31:34.601
reaches beyond
our personal ambitions.

396
00:31:37.562 --> 00:31:39.646
A Song of Ice and Fire.

397
00:31:42.150 --> 00:31:43.442
What?

398
00:31:44.902 --> 00:31:46.422
The coming war against
the darkness in the North.

399
00:31:46.446 --> 00:31:48.655
The Conqueror's Dream.

400
00:31:48.739 --> 00:31:50.866
Viserys shared it with me
when he named me heir.

401
00:31:50.950 --> 00:31:53.536
(struggles to breathe)

402
00:31:55.704 --> 00:32:00.793
My brother... was a slave
to his omens and portents.

403
00:32:00.876 --> 00:32:02.795
Anything to make
his feckless reign

404
00:32:02.879 --> 00:32:04.505
appear to have purpose.

405
00:32:08.258 --> 00:32:10.094
Dreams didn't make us kings.

406
00:32:10.595 --> 00:32:11.929
Dragons did.

407
00:32:14.931 --> 00:32:17.559
(tense music playing)

408
00:32:18.603 --> 00:32:21.439
(breathing heavily)

409
00:32:30.656 --> 00:32:32.200
He never told you...

410
00:32:32.283 --> 00:32:33.867
(panting)

411
00:32:35.286 --> 00:32:37.329
Did he?

412
00:32:38.163 --> 00:32:39.957
♪ ♪

413
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:18.954
I've had men whipped for
falling asleep on their watch.

414
00:33:25.127 --> 00:33:26.712
You are no man.

415
00:33:30.508 --> 00:33:33.344
You abandoned me...

416
00:33:34.970 --> 00:33:36.847
when I most needed you.

417
00:33:37.806 --> 00:33:40.017
Both our children
stolen from us.

418
00:33:41.518 --> 00:33:43.438
I needed you.

419
00:33:43.520 --> 00:33:44.540
Baela and Rhaena needed you.

420
00:33:44.564 --> 00:33:48.025
and you abandoned us
for more adventure at sea.

421
00:33:48.108 --> 00:33:50.027
As has always been your way.

422
00:33:51.988 --> 00:33:54.449
Corlys Velaryon:
I had no other place to turn.

423
00:33:55.866 --> 00:33:59.036
- I lost everything.
- We lost. Corlys.

424
00:34:01.037 --> 00:34:04.083
We.

425
00:34:14.886 --> 00:34:17.305
I understand we have a new king.

426
00:34:17.388 --> 00:34:20.892
The Stranger casts a long
shadow over this family.

427
00:34:27.272 --> 00:34:29.524
Your brother is also dead.

428
00:34:29.609 --> 00:34:32.236
(gasps. groans)

429
00:34:34.029 --> 00:34:37.075
In his haste to bury you
and claim your seat.

430
00:34:37.158 --> 00:34:38.658
he stood before the King

431
00:34:38.743 --> 00:34:41.578
and denounced Laenor's
sons as illegitimate.

432
00:34:42.788 --> 00:34:45.832
(sighs)

433
00:34:46.750 --> 00:34:49.212
- Daemon took his head for it.
- (scoffs)

434
00:34:53.883 --> 00:34:58.428
Heedless ambition has always
been a Velaryon weakness.

435
00:35:01.848 --> 00:35:04.685
You were right. Rhaenys.

436
00:35:06.479 --> 00:35:09.147
I reached too far.
And for nothing.

437
00:35:12.276 --> 00:35:17.239
Our pursuit of the Iron
Throne... is at an end.

438
00:35:20.743 --> 00:35:24.622
We shall declare for no one.

439
00:35:25.997 --> 00:35:28.334
We will retire to High Tide

440
00:35:28.417 --> 00:35:30.460
to be content...

441
00:35:30.544 --> 00:35:32.921
with our grandchildren and...

442
00:35:33.004 --> 00:35:35.258
Jace. Luke. and Joff are
claimants to the throne.

443
00:35:37.843 --> 00:35:40.846
Those boys'll not be safe
so long as Aegon is king.

444
00:35:43.140 --> 00:35:47.310
Rhaenyra was complicit
in our son's death.

445
00:35:48.937 --> 00:35:50.578
That girl destroys
everything she touches.

446
00:35:50.647 --> 00:35:53.526
That "girl"...

447
00:35:53.609 --> 00:35:56.863
is holding the realm
together at present.

448
00:35:56.946 --> 00:35:58.698
Every man standing
'round the Painted Table

449
00:35:58.781 --> 00:36:00.950
urges her to plunge
the realm into war.

450
00:36:02.326 --> 00:36:06.413
Rhaenyra's the only one
who's demonstrated restraint.

451
00:36:06.497 --> 00:36:07.808
Bartimos: The purpose
of war is to fill graveyards.

452
00:36:07.832 --> 00:36:09.000
my dear Lord St aunt on.

453
00:36:09.082 --> 00:36:11.752
The trick is to put
more of their men

454
00:36:11.835 --> 00:36:12.962
in the ground than your own.

455
00:36:13.044 --> 00:36:14.629
Easy words for a lord
who commands

456
00:36:14.714 --> 00:36:16.482
- from the safety of his castle.
- Doesn't make it any less true.

457
00:36:16.506 --> 00:36:17.841
Erryk: The Lord of the Tides!

458
00:36:17.924 --> 00:36:21.596
Lord Corlys Velaryon...

459
00:36:21.678 --> 00:36:25.140
and his wife.
the Princess Rhaenys Targaryen.

460
00:36:35.734 --> 00:36:38.194
My lords.

461
00:36:38.279 --> 00:36:40.614
Rhaenyra: Lord Corlys.

462
00:36:40.698 --> 00:36:43.326
It brings much relief to see
you hale and healthy again.

463
00:36:45.870 --> 00:36:49.165
I'm very sorry about
your father. Princess.

464
00:36:49.247 --> 00:36:50.832
He was a good man.

465
00:37:02.553 --> 00:37:04.680
Where is Daemon?

466
00:37:04.763 --> 00:37:07.808
There were other concerns which
demanded the Prince's attention.

467
00:37:08.475 --> 00:37:10.227
Mm.

468
00:37:19.152 --> 00:37:20.529
Your declared allies?

469
00:37:22.238 --> 00:37:25.826
- Yes.
- Too few to win a war for the throne.

470
00:37:27.243 --> 00:37:30.122
Well. we would also
hope to have the support

471
00:37:30.205 --> 00:37:32.486
- of Houses Arryn. Baratheon. and Stark.
- Corlys: Hope...

472
00:37:33.959 --> 00:37:35.585
is the fool's ally.

473
00:37:37.254 --> 00:37:40.383
Both Arryn and Baratheon
share blood with my house.

474
00:37:40.466 --> 00:37:42.593
But all of them
swore oaths to me.

475
00:37:42.676 --> 00:37:44.511
As did House High tower...

476
00:37:44.595 --> 00:37:45.096
if I remember.

477
00:37:45.178 --> 00:37:48.808
As did you. Lord Corlys.

478
00:38:02.613 --> 00:38:04.031
Your father's realm...

479
00:38:05.073 --> 00:38:08.076
was one of justice and honor.

480
00:38:09.035 --> 00:38:11.747
Our houses are bound
by common blood

481
00:38:11.830 --> 00:38:13.457
and common cause.

482
00:38:14.417 --> 00:38:18.129
This High tower treason
cannot stand.

483
00:38:23.676 --> 00:38:27.221
You have the full support
of our fleet and house.

484
00:38:28.848 --> 00:38:31.892
Your Grace.

485
00:38:36.480 --> 00:38:38.024
♪ ♪

486
00:38:38.107 --> 00:38:40.734
You honor me. Lord Corlys.

487
00:38:46.823 --> 00:38:48.951
Princess Rhaenys.

488
00:38:52.078 --> 00:38:56.709
But. as I said to my bannermen.

489
00:38:56.792 --> 00:38:57.584
I made a promise to my father

490
00:38:57.667 --> 00:39:00.629
to hold the realm
strong and united.

491
00:39:02.172 --> 00:39:03.841
If war's first stroke
is to fall.

492
00:39:03.924 --> 00:39:05.259
it will not be by my hand.

493
00:39:05.926 --> 00:39:07.303
You do not mean to act?

494
00:39:07.386 --> 00:39:11.848
Taking caution
does not mean standing fast.

495
00:39:11.931 --> 00:39:13.975
I wish to know who my allies are

496
00:39:14.060 --> 00:39:16.812
before I send them to war.

497
00:39:16.895 --> 00:39:18.939
♪ ♪

498
00:39:24.652 --> 00:39:26.154
The consequence of my...

499
00:39:26.238 --> 00:39:30.158
near-demise in the Step stones...

500
00:39:31.368 --> 00:39:33.788
is that we now control them.

501
00:39:33.870 --> 00:39:36.457
I took care to fully garrison
the territory this time.

502
00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:38.250
A total blockade
of the shipping lanes

503
00:39:38.334 --> 00:39:41.504
will be in place in days.
if not already.

504
00:39:41.587 --> 00:39:43.964
The Triarchy have been routed.

505
00:39:44.047 --> 00:39:46.133
The Narrow Sea is ours.

506
00:39:48.886 --> 00:39:51.638
If we...
further seal the Gullet.

507
00:39:51.721 --> 00:39:53.848
we can cut off all
seaborne travel and trade

508
00:39:53.933 --> 00:39:57.018
to King's Landing.

509
00:39:57.102 --> 00:39:59.687
I shall take Meleys
and patrol the Gullet myself.

510
00:40:04.776 --> 00:40:07.613
Bartimos:
When we drain the Narrow Sea.

511
00:40:07.696 --> 00:40:09.739
we can surround King's Landing.

512
00:40:09.823 --> 00:40:11.158
lay siege to the Red Keep.

513
00:40:11.241 --> 00:40:13.701
and force the Greens' surrender.

514
00:40:13.785 --> 00:40:18.332
If we are to have enough swords
to surround King's Landing.

515
00:40:18.415 --> 00:40:20.000
we must first secure the support

516
00:40:20.084 --> 00:40:21.228
of Winter fell. the Eyrie.
and Storm's End.

517
00:40:21.252 --> 00:40:25.004
I'll prepare the ravens.
Your Grace.

518
00:40:25.089 --> 00:40:28.424
Jacaerys:
We should bear those messages.

519
00:40:28.509 --> 00:40:31.553
Dragons can fly
faster than ravens

520
00:40:31.636 --> 00:40:33.263
and they're more convincing.

521
00:40:36.683 --> 00:40:37.977
Send us.

522
00:40:39.937 --> 00:40:41.855
The Prince is right. Your Grace.

523
00:40:45.817 --> 00:40:47.444
(tense music playing)

524
00:40:50.948 --> 00:40:52.073
Very well.

525
00:40:53.116 --> 00:40:56.120
Prince Jacaerys will fly north.

526
00:40:56.203 --> 00:40:58.598
First to the Eyrie to see my
mother's cousin. the Lady Jeyne Arryn.

527
00:40:58.622 --> 00:41:02.250
and then to Winter fell
to treat with Lord Cregan Stark

528
00:41:02.334 --> 00:41:03.494
for the support of the North.

529
00:41:05.462 --> 00:41:08.214
Prince Lucerys will fly
south to Storm's End

530
00:41:08.299 --> 00:41:11.218
and treat with
Lord Borros Baratheon.

531
00:41:11.301 --> 00:41:14.471
We must remind these lords
of the oaths they swore.

532
00:41:17.098 --> 00:41:20.018
And... the cost
of breaking them.

533
00:41:20.685 --> 00:41:22.479
♪ ♪

534
00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:45.311
It's been said
that as Targaryens.

535
00:41:45.335 --> 00:41:49.256
we are closer
to gods than to men.

536
00:41:51.299 --> 00:41:54.261
And the Iron Throne puts
us a touch closer. perhaps.

537
00:41:55.971 --> 00:41:59.892
But. if we are to serve
the Seven Kingdoms...

538
00:42:00.975 --> 00:42:03.770
we must answer to their gods.

539
00:42:03.854 --> 00:42:09.067
If you take this errand. you go
as messengers... not as warriors.

540
00:42:09.151 --> 00:42:11.611
You must take no part
in any fighting.

541
00:42:12.196 --> 00:42:14.156
Swear it to me now

542
00:42:14.239 --> 00:42:17.116
under the eyes of the Seven.

543
00:42:21.080 --> 00:42:23.122
I swear it.

544
00:42:27.127 --> 00:42:29.171
I swear it.

545
00:42:30.421 --> 00:42:33.466
Thank you.

546
00:42:34.218 --> 00:42:37.888
Cregan Stark is...

547
00:42:37.971 --> 00:42:39.199
close to your age than is mine.

548
00:42:39.223 --> 00:42:41.933
I would hope. that as men.

549
00:42:42.017 --> 00:42:44.018
you can find some
common interest.

550
00:42:44.102 --> 00:42:45.479
Yes. Your Grace.

551
00:42:54.738 --> 00:42:56.906
Storm's End is a short
flight from here.

552
00:42:58.575 --> 00:42:59.326
You have Baratheon blood

553
00:42:59.410 --> 00:43:02.288
from your grandmother. Rhaenys.

554
00:43:02.370 --> 00:43:03.663
And...

555
00:43:03.747 --> 00:43:06.959
Lord Borros is
an eternally proud man.

556
00:43:07.042 --> 00:43:08.167
He will be honored

557
00:43:08.252 --> 00:43:11.046
to host a prince of the realm...

558
00:43:11.129 --> 00:43:12.506
and his dragon.

559
00:43:20.680 --> 00:43:23.642
I expect you will receive
a very warm welcome.

560
00:43:25.268 --> 00:43:27.937
Yes. Mother. Y-Your Grace.

561
00:43:34.444 --> 00:43:37.323
(spirited music playing)

562
00:43:37.406 --> 00:43:39.158
Go to it then.

563
00:43:39.658 --> 00:43:42.035
(Vermax roars)

564
00:43:47.707 --> 00:43:48.750
♪ ♪

565
00:44:09.812 --> 00:44:11.064
(roars)

566
00:44:33.671 --> 00:44:35.797
(Daemon sings in Old Valyrian)

567
00:45:03.366 --> 00:45:05.076
(rumbling)

568
00:45:05.160 --> 00:45:06.995
(singing continues)

569
00:45:31.060 --> 00:45:32.645
(roaring)

570
00:45:46.033 --> 00:45:47.870
(singing continues)

571
00:45:53.207 --> 00:45:55.294
(Vermithor grumbles)

572
00:46:04.970 --> 00:46:06.555
(grumbles)

573
00:46:15.105 --> 00:46:16.732
(thundering)

574
00:46:39.171 --> 00:46:42.216
(roars)

575
00:46:58.105 --> 00:46:59.899
(Arrax grumbles)

576
00:47:03.111 --> 00:47:04.904
(Vhagar roaring)

577
00:47:20.462 --> 00:47:22.922
I am Prince Lucerys Velaryon.

578
00:47:23.006 --> 00:47:25.133
I bring a message to Lord
Borros from the Queen.

579
00:47:33.433 --> 00:47:36.812
(tense music playing)

580
00:47:42.276 --> 00:47:44.444
Baratheon Knight:
Prince Lucerys Velaryon.

581
00:47:46.404 --> 00:47:47.989
(thundering)

582
00:47:49.908 --> 00:47:54.370
Son of Princess
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

583
00:47:56.622 --> 00:47:57.415
(thunder continues)

584
00:47:57.499 --> 00:47:58.834
Lord Borros...

585
00:48:01.669 --> 00:48:04.589
I brought you a message
from my mother...

586
00:48:04.672 --> 00:48:06.966
the Queen.

587
00:48:07.049 --> 00:48:10.386
Yet earlier this day. I received
an envoy from the King.

588
00:48:11.471 --> 00:48:12.305
Which is it?

589
00:48:12.388 --> 00:48:15.142
King or Queen?

590
00:48:15.225 --> 00:48:18.979
The House of the Dragon does
not seem to know who rules it.

591
00:48:19.062 --> 00:48:20.230
(laughs)

592
00:48:21.022 --> 00:48:24.109
What's your mother's message?

593
00:48:30.239 --> 00:48:32.743
(sighs)

594
00:48:40.375 --> 00:48:41.877
Where's the bloody maester?

595
00:48:45.756 --> 00:48:46.839
(wind whistling)

596
00:49:16.787 --> 00:49:19.955
"Remind" me of my father's oath.

597
00:49:21.082 --> 00:49:23.794
King Aegon at least
came with an offer:

598
00:49:23.877 --> 00:49:26.087
My swords and banners
for a marriage pact.

599
00:49:28.047 --> 00:49:31.259
If I do as your mother bids...

600
00:49:31.343 --> 00:49:33.095
which one of my daughters
will you wed...

601
00:49:35.305 --> 00:49:37.556
boy?

602
00:49:37.640 --> 00:49:40.102
My lord...
I am not free to marry.

603
00:49:42.104 --> 00:49:43.562
I'm already betrothed.

604
00:49:45.649 --> 00:49:48.151
So you come with empty hands.

605
00:49:50.319 --> 00:49:52.406
Go home. pup.

606
00:49:52.488 --> 00:49:53.840
And tell your mother
that the Lord of Storm's End

607
00:49:53.864 --> 00:49:55.783
is not some dog
that she can whistle up

608
00:49:55.866 --> 00:49:59.287
at need to set against her foes.

609
00:50:01.540 --> 00:50:05.377
I shall take your answer
to the Queen. my lord.

610
00:50:10.756 --> 00:50:13.134
Prince Aemond: Wait...

611
00:50:15.011 --> 00:50:16.596
my Lord Strong.

612
00:50:20.558 --> 00:50:22.935
Did you really think

613
00:50:23.018 --> 00:50:25.855
that you could just
fly about the realm

614
00:50:25.939 --> 00:50:28.442
trying to steal my
brother's throne at no cost?

615
00:50:30.317 --> 00:50:32.821
I will not fight you.

616
00:50:32.904 --> 00:50:35.781
I came as a messenger.
not a warrior.

617
00:50:35.866 --> 00:50:37.576
A fight would be
little challenge.

618
00:50:40.662 --> 00:50:41.830
No.

619
00:50:41.913 --> 00:50:44.790
I want you to put out your eye.

620
00:50:46.752 --> 00:50:48.085
As payment for mine.

621
00:50:50.546 --> 00:50:52.883
One will serve.

622
00:50:56.720 --> 00:50:58.138
I would not blind you.

623
00:51:00.390 --> 00:51:03.477
Mm. plan to make a gift
of it to my mother.

624
00:51:07.855 --> 00:51:09.899
No.

625
00:51:09.982 --> 00:51:12.109
Then you are craven
as well as a traitor.

626
00:51:12.194 --> 00:51:12.944
Not here.

627
00:51:13.027 --> 00:51:13.819
Give me your eye

628
00:51:13.904 --> 00:51:16.989
or I will take it. bastard!

629
00:51:17.073 --> 00:51:18.116
Not in my hall!

630
00:51:19.910 --> 00:51:20.910
The boy came as an envoy.

631
00:51:20.951 --> 00:51:24.372
I'll not have bloodshed
beneath my roof.

632
00:51:24.455 --> 00:51:25.850
Take Prince Lucerys
back to his dragon.

633
00:51:25.874 --> 00:51:28.502
- (thundering)
- Now.

634
00:51:28.584 --> 00:51:30.629
♪ ♪

635
00:51:40.221 --> 00:51:42.015
(Arrax roars)

636
00:51:44.642 --> 00:51:46.227
(thundering)

637
00:52:03.118 --> 00:52:03.703
(grunts)

638
00:52:03.787 --> 00:52:06.622
(speaking High Valyrian)

639
00:52:27.227 --> 00:52:28.770
(thundering)

640
00:52:35.986 --> 00:52:37.279
(roars)

641
00:52:59.259 --> 00:53:01.093
(distant growling)

642
00:53:05.180 --> 00:53:06.473
(roars)

643
00:53:12.772 --> 00:53:15.107
(thundering)

644
00:53:31.665 --> 00:53:33.627
(Aemond laughs)

645
00:53:33.709 --> 00:53:35.754
(Vhagar roars)

646
00:53:37.129 --> 00:53:39.758
(intense music playing)

647
00:53:43.970 --> 00:53:46.680
- (grunts)
- (roars)

648
00:53:46.765 --> 00:53:48.642
(Aemond speaking High Valyrian)

649
00:53:51.560 --> 00:53:54.564
(roars)

650
00:53:55.522 --> 00:53:57.942
♪ ♪

651
00:53:58.026 --> 00:53:59.526
(Lucerys speaking High Valyrian)

652
00:54:00.611 --> 00:54:02.404
(grunts)

653
00:54:07.743 --> 00:54:10.788
(grunts)

654
00:54:12.832 --> 00:54:14.417
(laughing)

655
00:54:17.754 --> 00:54:20.799
(roars)

656
00:54:23.051 --> 00:54:24.761
Ugh!

657
00:54:24.843 --> 00:54:26.178
(roars)

658
00:54:32.227 --> 00:54:33.477
(roars)

659
00:54:36.064 --> 00:54:38.107
♪ ♪

660
00:54:40.609 --> 00:54:42.236
(thundering)

661
00:54:47.783 --> 00:54:49.035
(laughs)

662
00:54:51.120 --> 00:54:54.707
(Aemond speaking High Valyrian)

663
00:55:01.922 --> 00:55:03.799
(Lucerys speaking High Valyrian)

664
00:55:07.470 --> 00:55:11.390
(roars) -No. no. no.
no. no! No. Vhagar! No!

665
00:55:11.473 --> 00:55:12.642
(shouting command)

666
00:55:12.725 --> 00:55:15.687
Serve me. Vhagar! No!
(speaks High Valyrian)

667
00:55:25.821 --> 00:55:27.448
(screeches)

668
00:55:31.201 --> 00:55:32.287
(breathing heavily)

669
00:55:37.875 --> 00:55:40.754
Aemond: Vhagar! No! No...

670
00:55:40.837 --> 00:55:42.337
(roars)

671
00:55:50.013 --> 00:55:53.640
(tense music playing)

672
00:56:01.107 --> 00:56:03.734
(solemn music playing)

673
00:56:55.620 --> 00:56:57.413
♪ ♪

674
00:57:37.453 --> 00:57:40.080
(vengeful music playing)

675
00:57:47.796 --> 00:57:51.593
♪ ♪

